	in addition to the classical "plasma proteins," it contains all tissue
	proteins (as leakage markers) plus very numerous distinct immunoglobulin
	sequences, and it has an extraordinary dynamic range in that more
	than 10 orders of magnitude in concentration separate albumin and
	the rarest proteins now measured clinically. Although the restricted
	dynamic range of conventional proteomic technology (two-dimensional
