	formation are a function of the compositions of proteins as well
	as geochemical variables including temperature, pressure, oxygen
	fugacity and pH. The purpose of this study was to explore the dependence
	of metastable equilibrium states of protein systems on changes in
	the geochemical variables. Results: A software package called CHNOSZ
	implementing the revised Helgeson-Kirkham- Flowers (HKF) equations
	of state and group additivity for ionized unfolded aqueous proteins
	was developed. The program can be used to calculate standard molal
	Gibbs energies and other thermodynamic properties of reactions and
	to make chemical speciation and predominance diagrams that represent
	the metastable equilibrium distributions of proteins. The approach
	takes account of the chemical affinities of reactions in open systems
