	not seen in the Methanococcus comparison. Here, I compared the mesophilic
	bacterium Deinococcus radiodurans and its thermophilic relative Thermus
	thermophilus, which are similar in G+C content. Of the 190 pairs
	of amino acids, 83 exhibited significant substitutional asymmetry,
	consistent with the pervasive effects of selection. Most of these
	significantly asymmetrical pairs of amino acids were asymmetrical
	in the direction predicted from the Methanococcus data, consistent
	with thermal adaptation resulting from universal biochemical properties
